Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in mathematics would. Suppose that $x$ is an integer that satisfies the following congruences: \begin{align*}
3+x &\equiv 2^2 \pmod{3^3} \\
5+x &\equiv 3^2 \pmod{5^3} \\
7+x &\equiv 5^2 \pmod{7^3}
\end{align*}What is the remainder when $x$ is divided by $105$?
